{
  "texts": [
    "IntroductionIn recent years, the modeling of opinion dynamics has attracted the interest of researchers from different scientific fields, such as social sciences and mathematics.",
    "This growing popularity follows from the pervasive influence of social networks and global events that have shown how collective opinions can shape our society.",
    "For instance, the public debate around the use of vaccines during the COVID-19 pandemic has been characterized by the emergence of a significant number of conspiracy theories and misinformation, highlighting the importance of studying the processes behind opinion formation [35].",
    "In particular, it would be valuable to understand how collective opinions can polarize toward potentially dangerous, extreme opinions, or can converge toward a consensus.",
    "It is important to remark that individuals are constantly influenced by other people and by the media, and the evolution of their opinions strongly depends on their propensity to interact and discuss with others."
  ]
}